Review control description: (16) 'hybrid debt capital instrument' shall have the same meaning as defined in the
Reserve Bank of India (Non-Banking Financial Companies - Prudential Norms on Capital
Adequacy) Directions, 2025;

Review control description: (3) 'borrower' means any person or any entity who has been granted a housing loan
by any creditor institution or any other entity which may be specified by Reserve Bank of
India from time to time;

Review control description: (4) 'breakup value' means the equity capital and reserves as reduced by intangible
assets and revaluation reserves, divided by the number of equity shares of the investee
company;

Review control description: <image>
(9) 'default' means non-payment on the due date of any principal debt or interest
thereon payable by a borrower to any creditor institution;

Review control description: The Reserve Bank may cancel a certificate of registration granted to a MGC, if such
company -
(1) ceases to carry on the business of providing mortgage guarantee in India;

Review control description: or
(3) has failed to honour, in a timely manner, the claims arising from the contract of
guarantee it has entered into or may enter into;

Review control description: The essential features of a mortgage guarantee contract shall be as follows:
(1) it shall be a contract of guarantee under Section 126 of the Indian Contract
Act, 1872;

Review control description: Where the balance sheet of the investee
company is not available for two years, such shares shall be valued at ₹1/- per
company;
